Description
An index to evaluate model performances when the target variable is ordinal. 

Usage
new.index(pred_prob,y,m)

Arguments
pred_prob    The matrix of predicted probabilities on the test dataframe
y            The observed target values coded as numbers in 1:m
m            Number of ordinal classes


Value
new.index produces a quantitative number, the normalized version of the index and a plot of the actual prediction vs the perfect prediction (i.e. the observed values).


References
Ballante, E., Figini, S. & Uberti, P. A new approach in model selection for ordinal target variables. Comput Stat 37, 43â€“56 (2022). 
https://doi.org/10.1007/s00180-021-01112-4
